
*******************************************************************************
  plh - Plot proton spectra (M)
*******************************************************************************

      Syntax: plh<(pltmod)>

 Description: Plots a proton spectrum based on the parameters pltmod and intmod:
		pltmod='off' sets no plotting
		pltmod='fixed' takes sp and wp as is.
		pltmod='full' adjusts sp and wp to plot the full spectrum.	
		pltmod='standard' uses a complex macro for an "intelligent"
			output, adapted for a wide variety of spectra
			The parameter intmod is not in use for this mode
		pltmod='user' executes a macro named userplh, if defined
		pltmod='variable' adjusts sp and wp to plot all signals
		intmod='off' gives no integral
		intmod='full' gives a single integral over the entire spectrum
		intmod='partial' gives a series of integrals over each region
			(assumes that spectral regions have already been chosen)

    See also: System Operation, Chapter 6, "Display, Plotting, and Printing". 

     Related: intmod - Integral display mode (P)
              pltmod - Plotter display mode (P)
	      stdplh - Standard proton plot (M)
              sp - Start plot (P)
              wp - Width of plot (P)
